<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="style.css">
    <script src="index.js" defer></script>
    <title>Rule Engine</title>
</head>
<body>
    <h2>Create Rule</h2>
    <form id="createRuleForm">
        <input type="text" id="ruleInput" placeholder="Enter rule (e.g. age > 30 AND department = 'Sales')" required>
        <button type="submit">Create Rule</button>
    </form>
    <div id="createRuleResponse"></div>

    <h2>Evaluate Rule</h2>
    <form id="evaluateRuleForm">
        <input type="text" id="dataInput" placeholder='Enter data (e.g. {"age": 35, "department": "Sales", "salary": 60000})' required>
        <button type="submit">Evaluate Rule</button>
    </form>
    <div id="evaluateRuleResponse"></div>
    <button onclick="showRule()">show rules</button>
    <div id="ruleBook" style="display:none;">
    <h2>Rule Writing Guide</h2>
    <p>Use the following guidelines to create your rules:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>
            <strong>Comparison Operators:</strong>
            <ul>
                <li><code>&gt;</code> : Greater than (e.g., <code>age > 30</code>)</li>
                <li><code>&lt;</code> : Less than (e.g., <code>salary < 50000</code>)</li>
                <li><code>&gt;=</code> : Greater than or equal to (e.g., <code>age >= 18</code>)</li>
                <li><code>&lt;=</code> : Less than or equal to (e.g., <code>age <= 60</code>)</li>
                <li><code>=</code> : Equal to (e.g., <code>department = 'Sales'</code>)</li>
            </ul>
        </li>
        <li>
            <strong>Logical Operators:</strong>
            <ul>
                <li><code>&&</code> : AND (e.g., <code>age > 30 && department = 'Sales'</code>)</li>
                <li><code>||</code> : OR (e.g., <code>age < 30 || department = 'HR'</code>)</li>
            </ul>
        </li>
        <li>
            <strong>Grouping:</strong>
            <ul>
                <li>Use parentheses to group conditions (e.g., <code>(age > 30 && department = 'Sales') || (age < 25 && department = 'Intern'</code>).</li>
            </ul>
        </li>
        <li>
            <strong>Valid Rules:</strong>
            <ul>
                <li><code>age > 30 && salary < 60000</code></li>
                <li><code>department = 'Sales' || age < 25</code></li>
                <li><code>(age > 20 && age < 40) && department = 'Marketing'</code></li>
            </ul>
        </li>
        <li>
            <strong>Invalid Rules:</strong>
            <ul>
                <li><code>age > && salary < 60000</code> (missing operand)</li>
                <li><code>department = 'Sales' AND age <</code> (incomplete comparison)</li>
            </ul>
        </li>
    </ul>
</div>


    
</body>
</html>
